cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the performance of open-loop multi-antenna point-to-point links in ad hoc networks with slotted ALOHA medium access control (MAC), which involves the use of spatial multiplexing transmission and space-time block coded transmission. This is a key area of research in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with ad hoc networks, which are a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. The use of multi-antenna schemes with a simple decentralized slotted ALOHA MAC is also relevant to this category.
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with a network of multiple devices, which can be considered as a multiagent system. The use of a decentralized MAC protocol is also relevant to this category.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of a communication system, which can be considered as a control system. The use of linear maximum ratio combining and zero forcing receivers is also relevant to this category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of data over a wireless network, which can be considered as a multimedia application. The use of spatial multiplexing transmission and space-time block coded transmission is also relevant to this category.
